{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.37",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 37,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 37",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 37 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:1",
      "text": "At this also my heart trembleth, and is moved out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:2",
      "text": "Hear attentively the noise of his voice, and the sound that goeth out of his mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:3",
      "text": "He directeth it under the whole heaven, and his lightning unto the ends of the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:4",
      "text": "After it a voice roareth: he thundereth with the voice of his excellency; and he will not stay them when his voice is heard.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:5",
      "text": "God thundereth marvellously with his voice; great things doeth he, which we cannot comprehend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:6",
      "text": "For he saith to the snow, Be thou on the earth; likewise to the small rain, and to the great rain of his strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:7",
      "text": "He sealeth up the hand of every man; that all men may know his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:8",
      "text": "Then the beasts go into dens, and remain in their places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:9",
      "text": "Out of the south cometh the whirlwind: and cold out of the north.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:10",
      "text": "By the breath of God frost is given: and the breadth of the waters is straitened.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:11",
      "text": "Also by watering he wearieth the thick cloud: he scattereth his bright cloud:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:12",
      "text": "And it is turned round about by his counsels: that they may do whatsoever he commandeth them upon the face of the world in the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:13",
      "text": "He causeth it to come, whether for correction, or for his land, or for mercy.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:14",
      "text": "Hearken unto this, O Job: stand still, and consider the wondrous works of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:15",
      "text": "Dost thou know when God disposed them, and caused the light of his cloud to shine?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:16",
      "text": "Dost thou know the balancings of the clouds, the wondrous works of him which is perfect in knowledge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:17",
      "text": "How thy garments are warm, when he quieteth the earth by the south wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:18",
      "text": "Hast thou with him spread out the sky, which is strong, and as a molten looking glass?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:19",
      "text": "Teach us what we shall say unto him; for we cannot order our speech by reason of darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:20",
      "text": "Shall it be told him that I speak? if a man speak, surely he shall be swallowed up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:21",
      "text": "And now men see not the bright light which is in the clouds: but the wind passeth, and cleanseth them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:22",
      "text": "Fair weather cometh out of the north: with God is terrible majesty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:23",
      "text": "Touching the Almighty, we cannot find him out: he is excellent in power, and in judgment, and in plenty of justice: he will not afflict.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.37.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 37,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 37:24",
      "text": "Men do therefore fear him: he respecteth not any that are wise of heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
